1. Based on your chosen potential replace "???" in 'init.mod' and potential.mod. Keep these files in such a location so that they can access the potential files.

2. To run use <lammps executable file> in.elastic 

3. The log file will contain the information of the elastic constants at the end of the file. 

4. Read the preambles of "in.elastic" and "init.mod" files. Vary the value of "up" variable in init.mod upto +/- one order and check if the results are the same. 

 
 ==========================================================
 A=3.05737310140778379 --> Zener Anisotropy
 

    A=3.058A=3.058 indicates the material is elastically anisotropic.

    Isotropic materials have A=1

    A value A>1 means shear stiffness is relatively higher in [100][100] compared to [111][111] directions.
    
    
